parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: ABS warning light illuminates
brake pedal is hard to press
vehicle takes longer to stop
or vehicle does not stop at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of dealerships to properly repair recalled vehicles can lead to continued safety risks for drivers.
symptoms: Dealerships refusing to honor recalls
parts not available
or repairs not done correctly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to become stuck or inoperable, leaving the occupant unrestrained in the event of a crash, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The seat belt will not retract
the seat belt makes a loud noise
the seat belt becomes stuck
the seat belt will not release from the retractor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to become unsecured, leaving the occupant unrestrained in the event of a crash, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle will not latch or unlatch
the seat belt buckle becomes stuck
the seat belt buckle disconnects from the anchor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate seat belt restraint can cause the occupant to become unrestrained or partially restrained in the event of a crash, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The seat belt does not hold the child securely
the seat belt allows the child to move around
the seat belt does not provide adequate protection.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt anchor can cause the seat belt to become unsecured, leaving the occupant unrestrained in the event of a crash, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The seat belt anchor becomes loose
the seat belt anchor disconnects from the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the seat belt can cause the seat belt to become unsecured or inoperable, leaving the occupant unrestrained in the event of a crash, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The seat belt becomes stuck or inoperable intermittently
the seat belt retractor becomes stuck intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the steering wheel to fall off or become loose, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Steering wheel feels loose or falls off
steering column makes a knocking noise
excessive play in the steering
difficulty steering
airbag indicator light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The paint erosion and corrosion can lead to rusting of the vehicle's body, compromising its structural integrity and potentially causing safety issues.
symptoms: Paint wears off on the top of the vehicle
hood
and other areas
rusting through the metal
corrosion patterns on the vehicle's body.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of ball joints and starters can cause loss of control, accidents, and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Ball joints fail
starter fails
brake line breaks
side door falls off
oil and coolant leaks
outer rod end failure
transmission failure.
